- To install rails in our application 
```ruby
gem install rails 
```

- To create database files in rails
```ruby
rails db:create
```

- To open the console in the rails 
```ruby
rails console
```

- To generate scaffold in rails
```ruby
rails generate scaffold scaffold_name columname_1:datatype, columname_2:datatype,columnname_3:datatype,....,columnname_n:datatype
```

- when we create any data in seeds.rb file, To load all data from seeds.rb file to database we need to run the following command
```ruby
rails db:seed
```

- when we use any commands related to database or generate any data related to database then to commit them we use the following command 
```ruby
rails db:migrate
```

- To generate controller in rails 
```ruby
rails generate controller controller_name
rails generate controller admin
```

- To generate model in rails 
```ruby
rails generate model model_name column1:type column2:type column3:type

rails generate model customer 
```

- To install action-text in rails
```ruby
rails action-text:install
```

- To install action-storage in rails
```ruby
rails action-storage:install
```

 - To add a column in table
 ```ruby
rails generate migration AddColumnColumn_nameToTable Column_name:Datatype
```

- To see all the routes in rails
 ```ruby
rails routes
```

-To generate mailer
```ruby
rails generate mailer Mailername
rails generate mailer ProductMailer
```












